{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The plaintiff, Northwestern National Bank (Bank) is a Minneapolis Bank Corporation which wholly owns Northwestern Bank Building Co. (Bank Building Co.). (Stip. par. 1, 4 and 7). Bank Building Co. in turn owned the asset in question, approximately 10% (10,000 shares) of stock in The Center, Inc. (Center, Inc.). Center, Inc. owned a valuable building complex known as Northstar Center. (Stip. par. 8 and 9.)
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On December 16, 1965, a committee of the Bank\rquote s Board of Directors informed the Board that earlier that day the Directors of Center, Inc. had discussed the possible sale of Northstar Center. In the event of such a sale, the stock of Center, Inc. held by the Bank Building Co. would be of considerable value. The Bank\rquote s Board of Directors unanimously authorized the Bank\rquote s management to proceed with negotiations for the sale of the Bank Building Co.\rquote s stock investment in Center, Inc. (Stip. par. 10 and 11, Exs. A and B.)
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On December 22, the Bank\rquote s controller, Mr. Moorehead, addressed a memorandum to its president, Mr. Dissmeyer, suggesting that legal counsel be consulted and that a review of the \u8220\'3fpossible effects\u8221\'3f of the proposed sale of Center, Inc. stock had led him to \u8220\'3fsee three ways this could be handled and several legal questions.\u8221\'3f The three noted alternatives were said to be (1) sale of the Center, Inc. stock by the Bank building Co., (2) contribution of the stock by the Bank Building Co. to the Northwestern Foundation (Foundation), a Bank-sponsored Minnesota non-profit corporation which qualifies for the receiving of \u8220\'3fcharitable contributions\u8221\'3f as defined in \u167\'3f 170(3)(2) of the Code, followed by sale of the stock by the Foundation, and (3) 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
transfer of the stock by the Bank Building Co. to the Bank as a dividend, followed by the Bank\rquote s contribution of the stock to and its sale by, the Foundation.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (Emphasis added.) (Stip. par. 12, Ex. C.)
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
